The '''1973 [[Kent State Golden Flashes]] football team''' represented [[Kent State University]] in the 1973 college football season. The Golden Flashes offense scored 300 points while the defense allowed 131 points. Led by head coach Don James, the Golden Flashes were not ranked in the National Rankings. ==Regular season== ===Schedule=== {{CFB Schedule Start | time = no | rank = yes | ranklink = no | rankyear = 1973 | tv = no | attend = no }} {{CFB Schedule Entry | w/l = w | date = 9/15/1973 | nonconf = yes | homecoming = | time = no | rank = | away = | neutral = | opprank = | opponent = [[Louisville Cardinals football|Louisville]] | site_stadium = Dix Stadium | site_cityst = | gamename = | tv = no | score = 10-3 | overtime = | attend = }} {{CFB Schedule Entry | w/l = w | date = 9/22/1973 | nonconf = | homecoming = | time = no | rank = | away = | neutral = | opprank = | opponent = @ Ohio | site_stadium = | site_cityst = | gamename = | tv = no | score = 35-7 | overtime = | attend = }} {{CFB Schedule Entry | w/l = l | date = 9/29/1973 | nonconf = yes | homecoming = | time = no | rank = | away = | neutral = | opprank = | opponent = @ [[San Diego State Aztecs football|San Diego State]] | site_stadium = | site_cityst = | gamename = | tv = no | score = 9-17 | overtime = | attend = }} {{CFB Schedule Entry | w/l = w | date = 10/06/1973 | nonconf = | homecoming = | time = no | rank = | away = | neutral = | opprank = | opponent = @ Western Michigan | site_stadium = | site_cityst = | gamename = | tv = no | score = 39-15 | overtime = | attend = }} {{CFB Schedule Entry | w/l = w | date = 10/13/1973 | nonconf = | homecoming = | time = no | rank = | away = | neutral = | opprank = | opponent = Bowling Green | site_stadium = Dix Stadium | site_cityst = | gamename = | tv = no | score = 21-7 | overtime = | attend = }} {{CFB Schedule Entry | w/l = w | date = 10/20/1973 | nonconf = | homecoming = | time = no | rank = | away = | neutral = | opprank = | opponent = Eastern Michigan | site